definitions.definition: The tenth part of the increase arising from the profits of land and stock , allotted to the clergy for their support, as in England, or devoted to religious or charitable uses; a tax taking ten percent of land or stock profits, used for religious or charitable purposes.
A contribution to one's religious community or congregation of worship (notably to the LDS church).
